The theoretical framework described in this chapter provides a blueprint for numerical implementation. It demonstrates that the mathematical results of the thesis are amenable to computational verification, given an appropriate parameter set. No actual simulations are performed; the chapter merely outlines how such validation could be conducted in future work.


