Appendix C: Routh–Hurwitz Conditions for a 6th‑Order Polynomial

Consider the characteristic polynomial

P(\sigma) = \sigma^6 + a_5 \sigma^5 + a_4 \sigma^4 + a_3 \sigma^3 + a_2 \sigma^2 + a_1 \sigma + a_0.

The Hurwitz determinants are:

\begin{aligned}
\Delta_1 &= a_5,\\
\Delta_2 &= a_5 a_4 - a_3,\\
\Delta_3 &= a_5 a_4 a_3 - a_5^2 a_1 - a_3^2,\\
\Delta_4 &= a_4 \Delta_3 - a_5 (a_1 a_4 - a_2 a_5),\\
\Delta_5 &= a_3 \Delta_4 - a_5 (a_1 \Delta_4 - a_0 \Delta_3),\\
\Delta_6 &= a_0 \Delta_5.
\end{aligned}

All roots have negative real parts iff \Delta_i > 0 for i=1,\dots,6. A Hopf bifurcation occurs when \Delta_i > 0 for i=1,\dots,4, \Delta_5 = 0, and \frac{d\Delta_5}{d\theta} \neq 0 at the bifurcation point. These conditions are to be verified for the specific parameter regime.

