Appendix E: PBH Test for Controllability (Theoretical Statement)

For the linearized system (\dot{\xi} = J\xi + Bu) with B = [B_1, B_2, B_3], the PBH test states that the pair (J,B) is controllable iff for every eigenvalue \lambda of J, the matrix [\lambda I - J, \; B] has full row rank. This condition is assumed to hold for the combined control set, while it may fail for individual controls. The synergy theorem (Theorem 6.4) relies on the existence of a left eigenvector v for the unstable mode such that v^\top B_1 = 0 and v^\top B_2 = 0 but v^\top [B_1, B_2, B_3] \neq 0.

